Wash and dry all produce. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}(trimmed), separating
whites from greens. Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tsp} in a #small pot{} over
medium-high heat. Add scallion whites and cook until softened, ~{1%minute}. Stir in
@water{3/4%cup} and @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce
heat to low. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat
until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, trim, peel, and halve @Super Select cucumber{1} lengthwise.
Scoop out seeds with a #spoon{} and discard. Thinly slice cucumber crosswise. Place
in a #medium bowl{} and toss with @Asian sesame dressing{1.5%ounce}.

> Use all the dressing if preparing 4 servings.

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}. Place between two pieces
of #plastic wrap{} and pound with a #meat mallet{} or #heavy-bottomed pan{} until
1/2 inch thick. Season all over with @garlic powder{1%tsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

On a #shallow dish{}, combine @panko breadcrumbs{1/2%cup}, @cornstarch{1%tbsp},
and @salt{1/2%tsp}. Brush a thin layer of @mayonnaise{2%tbsp} onto both sides of
chicken (you may not use all the mayo). Working one piece at a time, press chicken
into panko mixture, coating all over.

> For 4 servings, use 1 tsp kosher salt.

Heat a 1/3-inch layer of oil in a large, preferably #nonstick pan{} over
medium-high heat. Once oil is hot enough that a pinch of breadcrumbs sizzles when
added to the pan, add chicken. Cook until panko is golden brown and chicken is
cooked through, ~{2-3%minutes} per side. Transfer to a #paper-towel-lined plate{}.

> For 4 servings, cook in batches.
> TIP: Thinner pieces will cook faster.

Place @katsu sauce{4%tbsp} in a #small microwave-safe bowl{}; microwave until warm,
~{20%seconds}. Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @butter{1%tbsp} and season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}. Divide rice, chicken, and cucumber between plates. Drizzle
chicken with katsu sauce to taste (or serve on the side for dipping). Garnish
chicken with scallion greens and serve.